quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  29,1,"Alif-L√£m-Mƒ©m"
  29,2,"Do people think once they say, вАЬWe believe,вАЭ that they will be left without being put to the test"
  29,3,"We certainly tested those before them. And Ћєin this wayЋЇ Allah will clearly distinguish between those who are truthful and those who are liars"
  29,4,"Or do the evildoers ЋєsimplyЋЇ think that they will escape Us? How wrong is their judgment"
  29,5,"Whoever hopes for the meeting with Allah, Ћєlet them know thatЋЇ AllahвАЩs appointed time is sure to come. He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  29,6,"And whoever strives Ћєin AllahвАЩs causeЋЇ, only does so for their own good. Surely Allah is not in need of Ћєany ofЋЇ His creation"
  28,85,"Most certainly, the One Who has ordained the Quran for you will ЋєultimatelyЋЇ bring you back home Ћєto MeccaЋЇ.¬†Say, вАЬMy Lord knows best who has come with ЋєtrueЋЇ guidance and who is clearly astray.вАЭ"
  28,86,"You never expected this Book to be revealed to you, but Ћєit cameЋЇ only ЋєasЋЇ a mercy from your Lord. So never side with the disbelievers Ћєin their disbeliefЋЇ"
  28,87,"Do not let them turn you away from the revelations of Allah after they have been sent down to you. Rather, invite ЋєallЋЇ to Ћєthe Way ofЋЇ your Lord, and never be one of the polytheists"
  28,88,"And do not invoke any other god with Allah. There is no god Ћєworthy of worshipЋЇ except Him. Everything is bound to perish except He Himself.¬†All authority belongs to Him. And to Him you will ЋєallЋЇ be returned"
